1
00:00:04,380 --> 00:00:06,260
I'm home.

2
00:00:06,260 --> 00:00:08,930
Welcome back. You're really late.

3
00:00:08,930 --> 00:00:11,260
Sorry I'm so late.

4
00:00:11,470 --> 00:00:12,470
Have you been drinking?

5
00:00:12,690 --> 00:00:13,720
Yeah.

6
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:16,180
Just a little.
I had a last-minute work thing.

7
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,480
I see.

8
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:23,020
Only my senior was supposed to go.
I didn't even have to be there.

9
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:25,030
But I was dragged along.

10
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:28,320
If you were going to be late,
you could've at least texted me.

11
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:29,900
I couldn't help it.

12
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,410
I'm just a rookie.
I didn't have a single chance to check my phone.

13
00:00:32,410 --> 00:00:34,080
Not once in five hours?

14
00:00:35,990 --> 00:00:38,330
Five hours,
and you didn't look at your phone even once?

15
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:39,330
You must've gone to the restroom at some point.

16
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,250
You've never worked in an office.

17
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:43,000
You wouldn't understand.

18
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:49,720
No, wait. I mean...

19
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:51,340
That was out of line.

20
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:53,800
I'm sorry.

21
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:58,060
It was really last-minute.
I was dragged out right after the meeting.

22
00:00:58,060 --> 00:01:00,810
Working in an office must be tough.

23
00:01:03,310 --> 00:01:06,570
Wow, this looks delicious.

24
00:01:06,570 --> 00:01:07,480
Can I have some?

25
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,740
Didn't you already eat?

26
00:01:08,740 --> 00:01:11,490
A rookie barely gets to eat anything.

27
00:01:13,530 --> 00:01:17,910
Should I heat it up?

28
00:01:17,910 --> 00:01:20,120
Should I heat it up?

29
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:23,170
No, I'm starving.
I'll just eat it like this.

30
00:01:26,710 --> 00:01:29,880
Actually, I'd prefer it hot.
Can you heat it up?

31
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:40,560
Students and office workers
really see things differently.

32
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:43,600
Waiting for someone to come home is exhausting, too.
